2.caption: 1976 Major League Baseball All-Star Game
2.description: The 1976 Major League Baseball All-Star Game was the 47th midseason exhibition between the all-stars of the American League (AL) and the National League (NL), the two leagues comprising Major League Baseball. The game was played on July 13, 1976, at Veterans Stadium in Philadelphia, Pennsylvania, home of the Philadelphia Phillies of the National League. The game resulted in a 7–1 victory for the NL.
2.inspected:Radio announcers: Jack Buck, Brent Musburger and Andy Musser
2.inspected:TV announcers: Bob Prince, Warner Wolf and Bob Uecker
